content: Definitely fun like the original, but when do we get a classic skin?

Fun nostalgia, but a bit different from the original. Thoroughly enjoy this game, but I8ss dropping the enemies in the castle to convert, the big Grey guys were better than the weird Pepsi guys. Don't regret my purchase one bit, but there does seem to be an issue with one achievement. I can't erase more than one enemy with one eraser. I have 1000+ wizards. I've tried dragging, rapid clicking, but can't get the 3 catapult 1 eraser achievement no matter what I try. Stuck at 59/60 because of it.

Fairly good simple game of defending ones own castle. Has a lot of potential of being the same as the wii version. However some of the ui/icons dont scale properly and look fairly compressed on a high resolution based display.
I played this long ago on the iPhone and am glad it finally showed up for Android. Intentionally bad graphics and sound = epic fun.
Love this game, I was sad when I switched to Android years ago and this game wasn't available.
Horrible, not like the desktop game on the xgen website at all. Complete waste of money, I hope my refund goes through.

This is a fun and funny game. I have found a probable bug in it, though. Touching either the credits or how to play button shows only the stick men running around. For as fun as that is to watch, this does prevent unlocking the Paying Your Dues achievement. This happened only in the version for Android. I have also purchased the version from Steam and it does not contain that bug. I do not know about the standalone version purchased from the Web site directly, as I did not purchase that version.
I'd like a way to turn off the sound please. thanks.
good port. its a game that was made for touchscreens. needs some UI changes, unclutter the screen. get local sound control so you can mute. allow more than 12 people to be stored
money well spent brings back memories, just wish there was more to do.
This is a blast from the past. Wonderful recreation of a classic.
About 50 percent happy. I lost my Pitt on level 3 and it never came back. Now I can't train new unites

I used to play this game when I was 13, years ago on Newgrounds! It's so odd, I never thought to look this up on Play Store until yesterday, May 6, 2019. Happened to be 9 days after it came out! The game is awesome! Great job! Love it! Must download for anyone! If i were able to add a tiny critique, I would love to be able to get rid of the word "Helth" next to the health bar. You guys did a fantastic job with this game! God bless you!
